Patch Set 5:

@JamesSimmons

No.  The issue is not RPMBINARGS, if the srpm is compiled for server configuration and the user doesn't have the right kernel or zfs during the %build stop configure will decide to build client modules instead.  This prevents that type of build from continuing.  This is protection against building the srpm downloaded by itself from doing a "bad thing".  Changing RPMBINARGS doesn't help that user.
